6
7 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
7 Section 13-116, which relates to use of corporal
8 punishment on certain students; prohibiting use of
8 corporal punishment on any student identified with
9 certain disability; removing language authorizing
9 certain waiver; providing an effective date; and
10 declaring an emergency.
10
11
11
12
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 13-116, is
14
15 amended to read as follows:
15
16 Section 13-116. A. School district personnel shall be
16
17 prohibited from using corporal punishment on students any student
17
18 identified with the most significant cognitive disabilities
18
19 according to criteria established by the State Department of
19
20 Education unless addressed in an annual individualized education
20
21 program (IEP) developed a disability in accordance with the
21
22 Individuals with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA).
22
23
23
24
24
Req. No. 3 Page 1
1 B. A waiver to the provisions of subsection A of this section
1
2 shall be granted if the parent or legal guardian of a student
2
3 provides written consent.
3
4 C. As used in this section, “corporal punishment” means the
4
5 deliberate infliction of physical pain by hitting, paddling,
5
6 spanking, slapping, or any other physical force used as a means of
6
7 discipline.
7
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
8
9 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9
10 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
10
11 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11
12 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
